The paper proposes a novel approach for representation learning on knowledge graphs using logic rules and paths. This involves mining rules from the KG and encoding them for representation learning, as well as using rules of different lengths to compose paths and create semantic associations among relations. This work involves machine learning, natural language processing, and database systems, which are all covered by the above sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI and cs.LG, followed by cs.DB, cs.CL, and cs.IR.
